{{Infobox football biography | name = JÃ©rÃ©my Berthod | image = | fullname = JÃ©rÃ©my Berthod | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1984|4|24}} | birth_place = [[Tassin-la-Demi-Lune]], [[France]] | height = {{convert|1.80|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}} | currentclub = [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre]] | clubnumber = 23 | position = [[Defender (association football)#Full back|Left back]] | youthyears1 = 1996â2002 | youthclubs1 = [[Olympique Lyonnais Reserves and Academy|Lyon]] | years1 = 2002â2007 | years2 = 2007â2008 | years3 = 2008â | clubs1 = [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]] | clubs2 = [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]] | clubs3 = [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre]] | caps1 = 74 | caps2 = 12 | caps3 = 50 | goals1 = 1 | goals2 = 0 | goals3 = 1 | nationalyears1 = 2002â2003 | nationalyears2 = 2003â2007 | nationalteam1 = France U19 | nationalteam2 = [[France national under-21 football team|France U21]] | nationalcaps1 = 15 | nationalcaps2 = 8 | nationalgoals1 = 3 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | pcupdate = 25 September 2011 | ntupdate = }} '''JÃ©rÃ©my Berthod''' (born 24 April 1984 in [[Tassin-la-Demi-Lune]], [[RhÃ´ne (department)|RhÃ´ne]]) is a [[France|French]] [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[AJ Auxerre]] as a [[Defender (association football)#Full back|left defender]].
==Football career== A product of the [[Olympique Lyonnais Reserves and Academy|Olympique Lyonnais youth academy]], Berthod made his [[Olympique Lyonnais|first team]] debut on 13 September 2003, in a 1&ndash;1 home draw against [[AJ Auxerre]]. He would go on to play a somewhat important part in the team's four consecutive [[Ligue 1]] titles (with the player's presence), and was also a regular selection for the [[France national under-21 football team|France U-21 squad]] during that timeframe.
In July 2007, l'OL agreed to transfer Berthod to [[AS Monaco FC]], for a fee of [[Euro|â¬]]2m.<ref>[http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/news/newsid=559297.html Berthod keen to start anew at Monaco]; UEFA.com, 6 July 2007</ref> He made his Monaco debut in [[2007&ndash;08 Ligue 1|the season]]'s second round, a 1&ndash;2 defeat at [[FC Lorient]], picking up a [[Penalty card#Yellow card|yellow card]] in the process, and finished the season with 12 league contests played.
After an unimpressive season at Monaco, Berthod made a summer move to Auxerre.<ref>[http://soccernet.espn.go.com/news/story?id=546723&&cc=5901 Berthod (Monaco) Ã Auxerre (Berthod (Monaco) to Auxerre)]; [[ESPN Soccernet]], 14 June 2008 {{fr icon}}</ref>
==Personal== Berthod's younger brother, [[Alexandre Berthod|Alexandre]], was also a footballer (and a defender), and also briefly represented Lyon.
